  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6595.91 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-38.3B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+39.3B), dealers are in forced buying mode as we're below their short gamma strikes in this breakout regime. The massive -23.4B total GEX and clustering of negative gamma from 6580-6590 means any downside pressure will trigger amplified dealer buying, while a push above 6605 flips dealers into selling mode against the rally. Watch 6590 as the critical inflection point - below here dealer buying accelerates, above 6605 they become sellers into strength.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves in either direction with dealers amplifying any breakout from the tight 6590-6605 range.",
